to see open ports :

sudo netstat -tulpn | grep LISTEN

to open port No---UFW (Uncomplicated Firewall) -install---status--enable--then
$ sudo ufw allow (port)/tcp

What is difference between awk and cut?
cut accepts a single-character delimiter, and is suitable only for very simple text file formats. 
Awk is much more versatile, and can handle somewhat more complex field delimiter definitions and even (in some dialects) a regular expression
